@wordwrap

@node Main "Preview V1.1"
                               @{" < Table of Contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

@{fg shine}Benifits:@{fg text}
   With this Macro you can view the Preview of a Document page with one mouse
   click.

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview Preview.iff"}:@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}P@{fg text}age View:
      The options are as follows in this order:
      - Page Width      : The view will alter so that the whole width of the
                          page can be seen of the monitor, whilst being as
                          large as possible.
      - Page Height     : Here the page will be displayed to show the full
                          height.
      - Edit Area Width : As before but with the Edit area width.
      - Edit Area Height: As before but with the Edit area height.

   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}pply
      The Document will the be zoomed to the appropriate size. All Changes,
      Scaling etc. will be done, so that the whole width of the Monitor that
      can be used will be used.

   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}ancel
      The Final Writer windows will return to the original view scale.

   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing the window
      The old window size will be used.
      All changes, Scaling etc. will be used.
      The macro will terminate.

@endnode
